Vice President Mike Pence visited the El Centro Station of U.S. Customs and Border Protection in California and addressed the issue of the migrant caravan from Central America. He emphasized that the caravan is a deliberate attempt to undermine the laws and sovereignty of the United States. Pence praised the men and women of Homeland Security for their dedication and promised the completion of the border wall. He also called on Congress to close immigration loopholes that are exploited by terrorists, traffickers, and criminals. Pence highlighted the dangers faced by Border Patrol agents and expressed the administration's commitment to their safety. He thanked the National Guard for their assistance in securing the border and expressed gratitude to the governors who have partnered with the administration in this effort. Pence concluded by acknowledging the bravery and sacrifices of the men and women protecting the border and promised that the administration will continue to stand with them in securing the nation.